0.6 g of chitosan powder was added to a 100 mL beaker with 15 mL of 2 wt% acetic acid solution and stirred to dissolve to a clear liquid and then adjusted the pH to 6. Then 60 mg (10 wt%) BHD solid powder was dissolved in 2 mL tetrahydrofuran solution and added drop by drop to the above chitosan solution, and the reaction was stirred at 70 °C for 3 h. The translucent film-forming solution was poured into a mould for casting and spreading, and the film was left at 45 °C for 10 h to obtain CSBHD hydrogel film (Fig. 1
                           ). A series of CSBHD hydrogel films were prepared by adding different contents of (5, 15, and 20 wt%) BHD in the same procedure and the results are shown in Table 1
                           .
